      public CompositeAggregationSpec(Consumer<org.opensearch.search.aggregations.support.ValuesSourceRegistry.Builder> aggregatorRegistrar, Class<? extends org.opensearch.search.aggregations.bucket.composite.CompositeValuesSourceBuilder<?>> valueSourceBuilderClass, Byte byteCode, org.opensearch.common.io.stream.Writeable.Reader<? extends org.opensearch.search.aggregations.bucket.composite.CompositeValuesSourceBuilder<?>> reader, org.opensearch.search.aggregations.bucket.composite.CompositeAggregationParsingFunction parsingFunction, String aggregationType)
      Specification for registering an aggregation in Composite Aggregation
      Parameters:
      aggregatorRegistrar - function to register the ValuesSource to aggregator mappings for Composite aggregation
      valueSourceBuilderClass - ValueSourceBuilder class name which is building the aggregation
      byteCode - byte code which is used in serialisation and de-serialisation to indentify which aggregation builder to use
      reader - Typically, a reference to a constructor that takes a StreamInput, which is registered with the aggregation
      parsingFunction - a reference function which will be used to parse the Aggregation input.
      aggregationType - a String defined in the AggregationBuilder as type.
